casebody.head_matter:
Josephat MUA, Petitioner,
v.
THE O'NEAL FIRM, LLP.
No. 19-6291
Supreme Court of the United States.
January 13, 2020
Motion of petitioner for leave to proceed in forma pauperis denied, and the petition for writ of certiorari to the District of Columbia Court of Appeals dismissed. See Rule 39.8. As petitioner has repeatedly abused this Court's process, the Clerk is directed not to accept any further petition in noncriminal matters from petitioner unless the docketing fee required by Rule 38(a) is paid and petition submitted in compliance with Rule 33.1. See Martin v. District of Columbia Court of Appeals , 506 U.S. 1, 113 S.Ct. 397, 121 L.Ed.2d 305 (1992) (per curiam ).
